Weapon and Armor Proficiency	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:ClassFeatures.AcolyteClassFeatures.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Acolytes are proficient with the club, dagger, staff, and the light and heavy crossbow. They are proficient with light armor but not with shields.	KEY:Acolyte ~ Weapon and Armor Proficiency																		AUTO:WEAPONPROF|Club|Dagger|Quarterstaff|Crossbow (Heavy)|Crossbow (Light)								SORTKEY:Class_Acolyte	SOURCEPAGE:DD
Spellcasting	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:ClassFeatures.AcolyteClassFeatures.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Acolytes gain access to a small number of divine spells. These blessings are much more limited in scope than a cleric's lists, as they tend to focus on daily necessities and conveniences rather than smiting evil. Acolytes prepare and cast spells as clerics. They use Wisdom to determine their spells' save DCs, the highest spell level they can cast, and any bonus spells they receive. If the acolyte has a 0 listed for a given level, add any bonus spells he receives to determine the total spells per day he can prepare and cast for that level. In essence, the acolyte cannot use spells of that level unless he gains bonus spells. Note that, unlike clerics, acolytes cannot spontaneously cast cure spells.	KEY:Acolyte ~ Spellcasting																										SORTKEY:Class_Acolyte	SOURCEPAGE:DD
Ward the Unholy	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:ClassFeatures.AcolyteClassFeatures.SpecialQuality.Supernatural	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:While acolytes lack a cleric's ability to blast the undead out of existence, they can call upon their gods' power to hold supernatural creatures at bay. %1/day, an acolyte can invoke his god's power to protect himself and his allies from fell monsters. He calls upon a divine blessing that grants him and all allies within 30 feet a +1 sacred bonus to AC and a +2 morale bonus to Will saves. To use this ability, the acolyte must have 5 gp worth of incense, holy water, and other religious paraphernalia on hand. These items are consumed when the acolyte uses this ability. Usually, it is easiest to total up the gp value of the acolyte's holy water and similar items and subtract 5 gp from them after each use of this ability. If the acolyte has less than 5 gp of these items on hand, this ability fails to function.|WardTheUnholyTimes	KEY:Acolyte ~ Ward the Unholy				DEFINE:WardTheUnholyTimes|0					BONUS:VAR|WardTheUnholyTimes|(AcolyteLVL+3)/3																	SORTKEY:Class_Acolyte	SOURCEPAGE:DD
Tend the Flock	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:ClassFeatures.AcolyteClassFeatures.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:By spending a full-round action chanting prayers and benedictions, the acolyte can calm others and steady their nerves. All allies within 60 feet of the acolyte who are 3 or more levels below the acolyte's total level gain a +4 morale bonus to Will saves, a +2 morale bonus to attacks, and a +2 morale bonus on all ability and skill checks. The acolyte can use this ability %1 per day and its effects last for 5 rounds + the acolyte's Charisma modifier (%2 rounds). The acolyte is skilled at managing large crowds and leading mobs of commoners and other folk who adhere to his faith.|TendTheFlockTimes|TendTheFlockDuration	KEY:Acolyte ~ Tend the Flock				DEFINE:TendTheFlockTimes|0	DEFINE:TendTheFlockDuration|0				BONUS:VAR|TendTheFlockTimes|2	BONUS:VAR|TendTheFlockDuration|5+CHA																SORTKEY:Class_Acolyte	SOURCEPAGE:DD
Strength of the Faithful	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:ClassFeatures.AcolyteClassFeatures.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:At 10th level, the acolyte is perhaps one of the most accomplished members of the church hierarchy. He has witnessed many miracles and seen the holy power of his god. His faith is unshakeable in the face of the horrors that lurk just beyond the knowledge of mortal men. He gains a +4 morale bonus on all saves against fear-based effects. In addition, %1 per day he can choose to automatically succeed at a single Will save against a fear-based effect.|StrengthOfTheFaithfulTimes	KEY:Acolyte ~ Strength of the Faithful				DEFINE:StrengthOfTheFaithfulTimes|0					BONUS:VAR|StrengthOfTheFaithfulTimes|1	BONUS:VAR|FearResistanceBonus|4|TYPE=Morale								ABILITY:Special Ability|AUTOMATIC|Resistance To Fear								SORTKEY:Class_Acolyte	SOURCEPAGE:DD
Weapon and Armor Proficiency	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:ClassFeatures.AlchemistClassFeatures.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Alchemists are proficient with daggers, clubs, staffs, and heavy and light crossbows. They have no proficiency with armor or shields.	KEY:Alchemist ~ Weapon and Armor Proficiency																		AUTO:WEAPONPROF|Club|Dagger|Quarterstaff|Crossbow (Heavy)|Crossbow (Light)								SORTKEY:Class_Alchemist	SOURCEPAGE:DD
Spellcasting	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:ClassFeatures.AlchemistClassFeatures.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Alchemists prepare and cast spells as per the wizard class. They gain an additional spell in their books with each level gained in this class. Intelligence determines the alchemist's maximum spell level, bonus spells, and spell save DCs. The core rules have complete details on spellbooks and how casters learn and prepare spells. If the alchemist has a 0 listed for a given level, add any bonus spells he receives to determine the total spells per day he can prepare and cast for that level. In essence, the alchemist cannot use spells of that level unless he gains bonus spells.	KEY:Alchemist ~ Spellcasting																										SORTKEY:Class_Alchemist	SOURCEPAGE:DD
Master of Alchemy	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:ClassFeatures.AlchemistClassFeatures.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:The alchemist never needs to spend skill ranks on Craft (alchemy). He gains 4 ranks in this skill at 1st level and one additional rank in it for each level gained in this class. However, the alchemist cannot violate the standard rules for determining the maximum ranks a character can have in a skill. Any ranks gained from this ability that would violate that cap are lost.	KEY:Alchemist ~ Master of Alchemy	DESC:&nl;Research Creature 1d20+%1|MasterOfAlchemistResearchBonus	DESC:&nl;Analyze Material 1d20+%1|MasterOfAlchemyAnalyzeMaterialBonus	DESC:&nl;Brew Mistures 1d20+%1|MasterOfAlchemyBrewMisturesBonus	DEFINE:MasterOfAlchemyResearchBonus|0	DEFINE:MasterOfAlchemyAnalyzeMaterialBonus|0	DEFINE:MasterOfAlchemyBrewMisturesBonus|0			BONUS:VAR|MasterOfAlchemyResearchBonus|2*AlchemistLVL+INT	BONUS:VAR|MasterOfAlchemyAnalyzeMaterialBonus|AlchemistLVL+INT	BONUS:VAR|MasterOfAlchemyBrewMisturesBonus|AlchemistLVL+INT	BONUS:SKILLRANK|Craft (Alchemy)|AlchemistLVL+3														SORTKEY:Class_Alchemist	SOURCEPAGE:DD
Weapon and Armor Proficiency	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:ClassFeatures.AntiquarianClassFeatures.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Antiquarians are proficient with the club, dagger, staff, light crossbow, and heavy crossbow. They gain no proficiency with armor or shields.	KEY:Antiquarian ~ Weapon and Armor Proficiency																		AUTO:WEAPONPROF|Club|Dagger|Quarterstaff|Crossbow (Heavy)|Crossbow (Light)								SORTKEY:Class_Antiquarian	SOURCEPAGE:DD
Item Lore	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:ClassFeatures.AntiquarianClassFeatures.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Antiquarians spend many long hours researching the manufacture and design of ancient relics, magical items, and other rare treasures. They gain several benefits from this training. They may use Intelligence, rather than Charisma, to modify their Use Magic Device skill. When employing enchanted items, they draw on their knowledge and training rather than their force of will or a blind exertion of their personality to activate them.	KEY:Antiquarian ~ Item Lore									BONUS:SKILL|Use Magic Device|max(INT,CHA)-CHA																	SORTKEY:Class_Antiquarian	SOURCEPAGE:DD
Arcane Expert	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:ClassFeatures.AntiquarianClassFeatures.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:At 3rd level, the antiquarian further hones his ability to manipulate and activate magical items. He gains the ability to re-roll up to three Use Magic Device checks per day. The antiquarian's knowledge and experience gives him insight that allows him to halt his efforts when he is on the verge of making a critical mistake. The antiquarian must opt to use this ability after rolling his check but before learning its result.	KEY:Antiquarian ~ Arcane Expert																										SORTKEY:Class_Antiquarian	SOURCEPAGE:DD
Catalog of Knowledge	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:ClassFeatures.AntiquarianClassFeatures.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:At 5th level, the antiquarian's knowledge of magical items and rare artifacts allows him to use his item lore ability with increased speed. He now divides an object's gp value by 400 to determine his Appraise DC and he may make his first check after only one hour.	KEY:Antiquarian ~ Catalog of Knowledge																										SORTKEY:Class_Antiquarian	SOURCEPAGE:DD
Weapon and Armor Proficiency	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:ClassFeatures.ApprenticeClassFeatures.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Apprentices gain proficiency with the club, dagger, staff, and light and heavy crossbows. They gain no proficiency with armor or shields.	KEY:Apprentice ~ Weapon and Armor Proficiency																		AUTO:WEAPONPROF|Club|Dagger|Quarterstaff|Crossbow (Heavy)|Crossbow (Light)								SORTKEY:Class_Apprentice	SOURCEPAGE:DD
Spellcasting	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:ClassFeatures.ApprenticeClassFeatures.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Apprentices prepare and cast spells as wizards. An apprentice must maintain a book of spells and gains a tome with 3 + the apprentice's Intelligence modifier 1st level spells and all 0-level ones. Intelligence determines the apprentice's bonus spells, spell save DCs, and maximum spell level.	KEY:Apprentice ~ Spellcasting																										SORTKEY:Class_Apprentice	SOURCEPAGE:DD
Weapon and Armor Proficiency	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:ClassFeatures.ArtisanClassFeatures.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:The artisan gains proficiency with the dagger, club, staff, and light and heavy crossbows. The artisan is not proficient with any armor or shields.	KEY:Artisan ~ Weapon and Armor Proficiency																		AUTO:WEAPONPROF|Club|Dagger|Quarterstaff|Crossbow (Heavy)|Crossbow (Light)								SORTKEY:Class_Artisan	SOURCEPAGE:DD
